uptime: Show how long the system has been running.
whoami: Print the current user's name.
hostname: Print or set system name.
ifconfig/ip: Display or configure network interfaces.
ping: Test a network connection.
traceroute/tracepath: Print the route packets take to network host.
netstat: Print network connections, routing tables, interface statistics, masquerade connections, and multicast memberships.
route: View and manipulate the IP routing table.
iptables/firewalld: Configure firewall rules.
journalctl: Query the systemd journal.
systemctl: Control the systemd system and service manager.
crontab: Schedule tasks to run periodically.
at: Schedule a command to be executed at a later time.
watch: Execute a program periodically, displaying output fullscreen.
nc (netcat): Utility for reading from and writing to network connections using TCP or UDP.
chmod: Change file permissions.
chown: Change file owner and group.
tar: Tape archiver for manipulating archives.
scp: Securely copy files between hosts on a network.
chroot: Run a command or interactive shell with a different root directory.
locate/updatedb: Find files by name.
ldd: Print shared object dependencies.
file: Determine file type.
basename: Strip directory and suffix from filenames.
dirname: Strip last component from file name.
bc: Arbitrary precision calculator language.
lsof: List open files.
htop: Interactive process viewer.
ssh-keygen: Generate SSH keys.
openssl: OpenSSL command-line toolkit.
ncdu: NCurses Disk Usage - a disk usage analyzer.
tac: Concatenate and print files in reverse.
fmt: Reformat paragraph text.
tr: Translate or delete characters.
paste: Merge lines of files.
cut: Remove sections from each line of files.
rev: Reverse lines character-wise.
sudo cp /dev/null mongod.log : for perticuler txt file data remove cmd
